HEADWORD: Carcajou
<hw>Car"ca*jou</hw> <pr>(k⟦aum⟧r"k⟦adot⟧*j⟦oomac⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[Probably a Canadian French corruption of an Indian name of the
wolverene.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>The wolverene; -- also
applied, but erroneously, to the Canada lynx, and sometimes to the
American badger. See <er>Wolverene</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

